description.narrative: UNICEF Haiti, with the goal of guaranteeing the right to identity of children, has continued in 2021 the activities to address the structural and situational challenges in the target councils of the three departments with the highest rate of unregistered children in Haiti.;The results achieved by the project have led to an improvement in the birth registration system in Haiti and an increase in the number of children under 18 registered in the civil offices.; Indeed, more than 35416; children under 5 years old were registered in 2021 at the civil registry. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
